17 /** Boxed value structures and functions to manipulate them
18  *
19  * @file src/lib/util/value.c
20  *
21  * There are three notional data formats used in the server:
22  *
23  * - #fr_value_box_t are the INTERNAL format. This is usually close to the in-memory representation
24  * of the data, though uint32s and IPs are always converted to/from octets with BIG ENDIAN
25  * uint8 ordering for consistency.
26  * - #fr_value_box_cast is used to convert (cast) #fr_value_box_t between INTERNAL formats.
27  * - #fr_value_box_strdup* is used to ingest nul terminated strings into the INTERNAL format.
28  * - #fr_value_box_memdup* is used to ingest binary data into the INTERNAL format.
29  *
30  * - NETWORK format is the format we send/receive on the wire. It is not a perfect representation
31  * of data packing for all protocols, so you will likely need to overload conversion for some types.
32  * - fr_value_box_to_network is used to covert INTERNAL format data to generic NETWORK format data.
33  * For uint32s, IP addresses etc... This means BIG ENDIAN uint8 ordering.
34  * - fr_value_box_from_network is used to convert packet buffer fragments in NETWORK format to
35  * INTERNAL format.
36  *
37  * - PRESENTATION format is what we print to the screen, and what we get from the user, databases
38  * and configuration files.
39  * - #fr_value_box_aprint is used to convert from INTERNAL to PRESENTATION format.
40  * - #fr_value_box_from_str is used to convert from PRESENTATION to INTERNAL format.
41  *
42  * @copyright 2014-2017 The FreeRADIUS server project
43  * @copyright 2017 Arran Cudbard-Bell (a.cudbardb@freeradius.org)
44  */

482 /** Copy flags and type data from one value box to another
483  *
484  * @param[in] dst to copy flags to
485  * @param[in] src of data.
486  */
487 static inline void fr_value_box_copy_meta(fr_value_box_t *dst, fr_value_box_t const *src)
488 {
489  switch (src->type) {
490  case FR_TYPE_VARIABLE_SIZE:
491  dst->vb_length = src->vb_length;
492  break;
493 
494  default:
495  break;
496  }
497 
498  dst->enumv = src->enumv;
499  dst->type = src->type;
500  dst->tainted = src->tainted;
501  dst->next = NULL; /* copy one */
502 }
503 
504 /** Compare two values
505  *
506  * @param[in] a Value to compare.
507  * @param[in] b Value to compare.
508  * @return
509  * - -1 if a is less than b.
510  * - 0 if both are equal.
511  * - 1 if a is more than b.
512  * - < -1 on failure.
513  */
514 int fr_value_box_cmp(fr_value_box_t const *a, fr_value_box_t const *b)
515 {
516  int compare = 0;
517 
518  if (!fr_cond_assert(a->type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
519  if (!fr_cond_assert(b->type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
520 
521  if (a->type != b->type) {
522  fr_strerror_printf("%s: Can't compare values of different types", __FUNCTION__);
523  return -2;
524  }
525 
526  /*
527  * After doing the previous check for special comparisons,
528  * do the per-type comparison here.
529  */
530  switch (a->type) {
531  case FR_TYPE_VARIABLE_SIZE:
532  {
533  size_t length;
534 
535  if (a->vb_length < b->vb_length) {
536  length = a->vb_length;
537  } else {
538  length = b->vb_length;
539  }
540 
541  if (length) {
542  compare = memcmp(a->vb_octets, b->vb_octets, length);
543  if (compare != 0) break;
544  }
545 
546  /*
547  * Contents are the same. The return code
548  * is therefore the difference in lengths.
549  *
550  * i.e. "0x00" is smaller than "0x0000"
551  */
552  compare = a->vb_length - b->vb_length;
553  }
554  break;
555 
556  /*
557  * Short-hand for simplicity.
558  */
559 #define CHECK(_type) if (a->datum._type < b->datum._type) { compare = -1; \
560  } else if (a->datum._type > b->datum._type) { compare = +1; }
561 
562  case FR_TYPE_BOOL:
563  CHECK(boolean);
564  break;
565 
566  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
567  CHECK(date);
568  break;
569 
570  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
571  CHECK(uint8);
572  break;
573 
574  case FR_TYPE_UINT16:
575  CHECK(uint16);
576  break;
577 
578  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
579  CHECK(int32);
580  break;
581 
582  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
583  CHECK(uint64);
584  break;
585 
586  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
587  CHECK(int8);
588  break;
589 
590  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
591  CHECK(int16);
592  break;
593 
594  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
595  CHECK(int32);
596  break;
597 
598  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
599  CHECK(int64);
600  break;
601 
602  case FR_TYPE_SIZE:
603  CHECK(size);
604  break;
605 
606  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
607  CHECK(time_delta);
608  break;
609 
610  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT32:
611  CHECK(float32);
612  break;
613 
614  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT64:
615  CHECK(float64);
616  break;
617 
618  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
619  compare = memcmp(a->vb_ether, b->vb_ether, sizeof(a->vb_ether));
620  break;
621 
622  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
623  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
624  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
625  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
626  compare = memcmp(&a->vb_ip, &b->vb_ip, sizeof(a->vb_ip));
627  break;
628 
629  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
630  compare = memcmp(a->vb_ifid, b->vb_ifid, sizeof(a->vb_ifid));
631  break;
632 
633  /*
634  * These should be handled at some point
635  */
636  case FR_TYPE_NON_VALUES:
637  (void)fr_cond_assert(0); /* unknown type */
638  return -2;
639 
640  /*
641  * Do NOT add a default here, as new types are added
642  * static analysis will warn us they're not handled
643  */
644  }
645 
646  if (compare > 0) return 1;
647  if (compare < 0) return -1;
648  return 0;
649 }
650 
651 /*
652  * We leverage the fact that IPv4 and IPv6 prefixes both
653  * have the same format:
654  *
655  * reserved, prefix-len, data...
656  */
657 static int fr_value_box_cidr_cmp_op(fr_token_t op, int bytes,
658  uint8_t a_net, uint8_t const *a,
659  uint8_t b_net, uint8_t const *b)
660 {
661  int i, common;
662  uint32_t mask;
663 
664  /*
665  * Handle the case of netmasks being identical.
666  */
667  if (a_net == b_net) {
668  int compare;
669 
670  compare = memcmp(a, b, bytes);
671 
672  /*
673  * If they're identical return true for
674  * identical.
675  */
676  if ((compare == 0) &&
677  ((op == T_OP_CMP_EQ) ||
678  (op == T_OP_LE) ||
679  (op == T_OP_GE))) {
680  return true;
681  }
682 
683  /*
684  * Everything else returns false.
685  *
686  * 10/8 == 24/8 --> false
687  * 10/8 <= 24/8 --> false
688  * 10/8 >= 24/8 --> false
689  */
690  return false;
691  }
692 
693  /*
694  * Netmasks are different. That limits the
695  * possible results, based on the operator.
696  */
697  switch (op) {
698  case T_OP_CMP_EQ:
699  return false;
700 
701  case T_OP_NE:
702  return true;
703 
704  case T_OP_LE:
705  case T_OP_LT: /* 192/8 < 192.168/16 --> false */
706  if (a_net < b_net) {
707  return false;
708  }
709  break;
710 
711  case T_OP_GE:
712  case T_OP_GT: /* 192/16 > 192.168/8 --> false */
713  if (a_net > b_net) {
714  return false;
715  }
716  break;
717 
718  default:
719  return false;
720  }
721 
722  if (a_net < b_net) {
723  common = a_net;
724  } else {
725  common = b_net;
726  }
727 
728  /*
729  * Do the check uint8 by uint8. If the bytes are
730  * identical, it MAY be a match. If they're different,
731  * it is NOT a match.
732  */
733  i = 0;
734  while (i < bytes) {
735  /*
736  * All leading bytes are identical.
737  */
738  if (common == 0) return true;
739 
740  /*
741  * Doing bitmasks takes more work.
742  */
743  if (common < 8) break;
744 
745  if (a[i] != b[i]) return false;
746 
747  common -= 8;
748  i++;
749  continue;
750  }
751 
752  mask = 1;
753  mask <<= (8 - common);
754  mask--;
755  mask = ~mask;
756 
757  if ((a[i] & mask) == ((b[i] & mask))) {
758  return true;
759  }
760 
761  return false;
762 }
763 
764 /** Compare two attributes using an operator
765  *
766  * @param[in] op to use in comparison.
767  * @param[in] a Value to compare.
768  * @param[in] b Value to compare.
769  * @return
770  * - 1 if true
771  * - 0 if false
772  * - -1 on failure.
773  */
774 int fr_value_box_cmp_op(fr_token_t op, fr_value_box_t const *a, fr_value_box_t const *b)
775 {
776  int compare = 0;
777 
778  if (!a || !b) return -1;
779 
780  if (!fr_cond_assert(a->type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
781  if (!fr_cond_assert(b->type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
782 
783  switch (a->type) {
784  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
785  switch (b->type) {
786  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR: /* IPv4 and IPv4 */
787  goto cmp;
788 
789  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX: /* IPv4 and IPv4 Prefix */
790  return fr_value_box_cidr_cmp_op(op, 4, 32, (uint8_t const *) &a->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr,
791  b->vb_ip.prefix, (uint8_t const *) &b->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr);
792 
793  default:
794  fr_strerror_printf("Cannot compare IPv4 with IPv6 address");
795  return -1;
796  }
797 
798  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX: /* IPv4 and IPv4 Prefix */
799  switch (b->type) {
800  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
801  return fr_value_box_cidr_cmp_op(op, 4, a->vb_ip.prefix,
802  (uint8_t const *) &a->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr,
803  32, (uint8_t const *) &b->vb_ip.addr.v4);
804 
805  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX: /* IPv4 Prefix and IPv4 Prefix */
806  return fr_value_box_cidr_cmp_op(op, 4, a->vb_ip.prefix,
807  (uint8_t const *) &a->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr,
808  b->vb_ip.prefix, (uint8_t const *) &b->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr);
809 
810  default:
811  fr_strerror_printf("Cannot compare IPv4 with IPv6 address");
812  return -1;
813  }
814 
815  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
816  switch (b->type) {
817  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR: /* IPv6 and IPv6 */
818  goto cmp;
819 
820  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX: /* IPv6 and IPv6 Preifx */
821  return fr_value_box_cidr_cmp_op(op, 16, 128, (uint8_t const *) &a->vb_ip.addr.v6,
822  b->vb_ip.prefix, (uint8_t const *) &b->vb_ip.addr.v6);
823 
824  default:
825  fr_strerror_printf("Cannot compare IPv6 with IPv4 address");
826  return -1;
827  }
828 
829  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
830  switch (b->type) {
831  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR: /* IPv6 Prefix and IPv6 */
832  return fr_value_box_cidr_cmp_op(op, 16, a->vb_ip.prefix,
833  (uint8_t const *) &a->vb_ip.addr.v6,
834  128, (uint8_t const *) &b->vb_ip.addr.v6);
835 
836  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX: /* IPv6 Prefix and IPv6 */
837  return fr_value_box_cidr_cmp_op(op, 16, a->vb_ip.prefix,
838  (uint8_t const *) &a->vb_ip.addr.v6,
839  b->vb_ip.prefix, (uint8_t const *) &b->vb_ip.addr.v6);
840 
841  default:
842  fr_strerror_printf("Cannot compare IPv6 with IPv4 address");
843  return -1;
844  }
845 
846  default:
847  cmp:
848  compare = fr_value_box_cmp(a, b);
849  if (compare < -1) { /* comparison error */
850  return -1;
851  }
852  }
853 
854  /*
855  * Now do the operator comparison.
856  */
857  switch (op) {
858  case T_OP_CMP_EQ:
859  return (compare == 0);
860 
861  case T_OP_NE:
862  return (compare != 0);
863 
864  case T_OP_LT:
865  return (compare < 0);
866 
867  case T_OP_GT:
868  return (compare > 0);
869 
870  case T_OP_LE:
871  return (compare <= 0);
872 
873  case T_OP_GE:
874  return (compare >= 0);
875 
876  default:
877  return 0;
878  }
879 }

883 /** Convert a string value with escape sequences into its binary form
884  *
885  * The quote character determines the escape sequences recognised.
886  *
887  * - Literal mode ("'" quote char) will unescape:
888  @verbatim
889  - \\ - Literal backslash.
890  - <quote> - The quotation char.
891  @endverbatim
892  * - Expanded mode ('"' quote char) will also unescape:
893  @verbatim
894  - \a - Alert.
895  - \b - Backspace.
896  - \e - Escape character i.e. (\)
897  - \r - Carriage return.
898  - \n - Newline.
899  - \t - Tab.
900  - \v - Vertical tab
901  - <oct> - An octal escape sequence.
902  - \x<hex> - A hex escape sequence.
903  @endverbatim
904  * - Backtick mode ('`' quote char) identical to expanded mode.
905  * - Regex mode ('/') identical to expanded mode but two successive
906  * backslashes will be interpreted as an escape sequence, but not
907  * unescaped, so that they will be passed to the underlying regex
908  * library.
909  * - Verbatim mode ('\0' quote char) copies in to out verbatim.
910  *
911  * @note The resulting output may contain embedded \0s.
912  * @note Unrecognised escape sequences will be copied verbatim.
913  * @note In and out may point to the same underlying buffer.
914  * @note Copying will stop early if an unescaped instance of the
915  * quoting char is found in the input buffer.
916  *
917  * @param[out] out Where to write the unescaped string.
918  * @param[in] in The string to unescape.
919  * @param[in] inlen Length of input string. Pass SIZE_MAX to copy all data
920  * in the input buffer.
921  * @param[in] quote Character around the string, determines unescaping mode.
922  *
923  * @return
924  * - 0 if input string was empty.
925  * - >0 the number of bytes written to out.
926  */
927 size_t fr_value_str_unescape(fr_sbuff_t *out, fr_sbuff_t *in, size_t inlen, char quote)
928 {
929  switch (quote) {
930  default:
931  break;
932 
933  case '"':
934  {
935  return fr_sbuff_out_unescape_until(out, in, inlen, NULL, &fr_value_unescape_double);
936  }
937  case '\'':
938  {
939  return fr_sbuff_out_unescape_until(out, in, inlen, NULL, &fr_value_unescape_single);
940  }
941 
942  case '`':
943  {
944  return fr_sbuff_out_unescape_until(out, in, inlen, NULL, &fr_value_unescape_backtick);
945  }
946 
947  case '/':
948  {
949  return fr_sbuff_out_unescape_until(out, in, inlen, NULL, &fr_value_unescape_solidus);
950  }
951  }
952 
953  return fr_sbuff_out_bstrncpy(out, in, inlen);
954 }

1022 /** Performs byte order reversal for types that need it
1023  *
1024  * @param[in] dst Where to write the result. May be the same as src.
1025  * @param[in] src #fr_value_box_t containing an uint32 value.
1026  * @return
1027  * - 0 on success.
1028  * - -1 on failure.
1029  */
1030 int fr_value_box_hton(fr_value_box_t *dst, fr_value_box_t const *src)
1031 {
1032  if (!fr_cond_assert(src->type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
1033 
1034  switch (src->type) {
1035  default:
1036  break;
1037 
1038  case FR_TYPE_BOOL:
1039  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
1040  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
1041  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
1042  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
1043  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
1044  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
1045  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
1046  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
1047  case FR_TYPE_SIZE:
1048  fr_value_box_copy(NULL, dst, src);
1049  return 0;
1050 
1051  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
1052  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
1053  case FR_TYPE_NON_VALUES:

1057

1060  * initialise the destination box
1061  * with similar meta data as the src.
1062  *
1063  * Don't use the copy meta data function

1066  */

1072  break;

1076  break;
1077

1080  break;
1081 
1082  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
1083  dst->vb_uint16 = htons(src->vb_uint16);
1084  break;
1085 
1086  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
1087  dst->vb_uint32 = htonl(src->vb_uint32);
1088  break;
1089 
1090  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
1091  dst->vb_date = htonll(src->vb_date);
1092  break;
1093 
1094  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
1095  dst->vb_time_delta = htonll(src->vb_time_delta);
1096  break;
1097 
1098  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
1099  dst->vb_uint64 = htonll(src->vb_uint64);
1100  break;
1101 
1102  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT32:
1103  dst->vb_float32 = htonl((uint32_t)src->vb_float32);
1104  break;
1105 
1106  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT64:
1107  dst->vb_float64 = htonll((uint64_t)src->vb_float64);
1108  break;
1109 
1110  default:
1111  fr_assert_fail(NULL);

1134 /** Encode a single value box, serializing its contents in generic network format
1135  *
1136  * The serialized form of #fr_value_box_t may not match the requirements of your protocol
1137  * completely. In cases where they do not, you should overload specific types in the
1138  * function calling #fr_value_box_to_network.
1139  *
1140  * The general serialization rules are:
1141  *
1142  * - Octets are encoded in binary form (not hex).
1143  * - Strings are encoded without the trailing \0 byte.
1144  * - Integers are encoded big-endian.
1145  * - Bools are encoded using one byte, with value 0x00 (false) or 0x01 (true).
1146  * - Signed integers are encoded two's complement, with the MSB as the sign bit.
1147  * Byte order is big-endian.
1148  * - Network addresses are encoded big-endian.
1149  * - IPv4 prefixes are encoded with 1 byte for the prefix, then 4 bytes of address.
1150  * - IPv6 prefixes are encoded with 1 byte for the scope_id, 1 byte for the prefix,
1151  * and 16 bytes of address.
1152  * - Floats are encoded in IEEE-754 format with a big-endian byte order. We rely
1153  * on the fact that the C standards require floats to be represented in IEEE-754
1154  * format in memory.
1155  * - Dates are encoded as 16/32/64-bit unsigned UNIX timestamps.
1156  * - time_deltas are encoded as 16/32/64-bit signed integers.
1157  *
1158  * #FR_TYPE_SIZE is not encodable, as it is system specific.
1159  *
1160  * This function will not encode complex types (TLVs, VSAs etc...). These are usually
1161  * specific to the protocol anyway.
1162  *
1163  * @param[out] need if not NULL, how many bytes are required to serialize
1164  * the remainder of the boxed data.
1165  * Note: Only variable length types will be partially
1166  * encoded. Fixed length types will not be partially encoded.
1167  * @param[out] dst Where to write serialized data.
1168  * @param[in] dst_len The length of the output buffer, or maximum value fragment
1169  * size.
1170  * @param[in] value to encode.
1171  * @return
1172  * - 0 no bytes were written, see need value to determine if it was because
1173  * the fr_value_box_t was #FR_TYPE_OCTETS/#FR_TYPE_STRING and was
1174  * NULL (which is unfortunately valid)
1175  * - >0 the number of bytes written to out.
1176  * - <0 on error.
1177  */
1178 ssize_t fr_value_box_to_network(size_t *need, uint8_t *dst, size_t dst_len, fr_value_box_t const *value)
1179 {
1180  return fr_value_box_to_network_dbuff(need, &FR_DBUFF_TMP(dst, dst_len), value);
1181 }
1182 
1183 ssize_t fr_value_box_to_network_dbuff(size_t *need, fr_dbuff_t *dbuff, fr_value_box_t const *value)
1184 {
1185  size_t min, max;
1186 
1187  /*
1188  * Variable length types
1189  */
1190  switch (value->type) {
1191  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
1192  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
1193  {
1194  size_t len;
1195 
1196  /*
1197  * Figure dst if we'd overflow
1198  */
1199  if (value->vb_length > fr_dbuff_extend_lowat(NULL, dbuff, value->vb_length)) {
1200  if (need) *need = value->vb_length;
1201  len = fr_dbuff_remaining(dbuff);
1202  } else {
1203  if (need) *need = 0;
1204  len = value->vb_length;
1205  }
1206 
1207  if (value->vb_length > 0) fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, (uint8_t const *)value->datum.ptr, len);
1208 
1209  return len;
1210  }
1211 
1212  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
1213  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
1214  if (value->enumv) {
1215  min = max = value->enumv->flags.length;
1216  } else {
1217  min = max = 4;
1218  }
1219  break;
1220 
1221  default:
1222  min = fr_value_box_network_sizes[value->type][0];
1223  max = fr_value_box_network_sizes[value->type][1];
1224  break;
1225  }
1226 
1227  /*
1228  * It's an unsupported type
1229  */
1230  if ((min == 0) && (max == 0)) {
1231  unsupported:
1232  fr_strerror_printf("%s: Cannot encode type \"%s\"",
1233  __FUNCTION__,
1234  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, value->type, "<INVALID>"));
1235  return FR_VALUE_BOX_NET_ERROR;
1236  }
1237 
1238  /*
1239  * Fixed type would overflow output buffer
1240  */
1241  if (max > fr_dbuff_extend_lowat(NULL, dbuff, max)) {
1242  if (need) *need = max;
1243  return 0;
1244  }
1245 
1246  switch (value->type) {
1247  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
1248  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, (uint8_t const *)&value->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr,
1249  sizeof(value->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
1250  break;
1251  /*
1252  * Needs special mangling
1253  */
1254  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
1255  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, &value->vb_ip.prefix, sizeof(value->vb_ip.prefix));
1256  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, (uint8_t const *)&value->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr,
1257  sizeof(value->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
1258  break;
1259 
1260  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
1261  if (value->vb_ip.scope_id > 0) fr_dbuff_in_bytes(dbuff, value->vb_ip.scope_id);
1262  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, value->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, sizeof(value->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr));
1263  break;
1264 
1265  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
1266  if (value->vb_ip.scope_id > 0) fr_dbuff_in_bytes(dbuff, value->vb_ip.scope_id);
1267  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, &value->vb_ip.prefix, sizeof(value->vb_ip.prefix));
1268  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, value->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, sizeof(value->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr));
1269  break;
1270 
1271  case FR_TYPE_BOOL:
1272  fr_dbuff_in_bytes(dbuff, value->datum.boolean);
1273  break;
1274 
1275  /*
1276  * Already in network byte-order
1277  */
1278 
1279  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
1280  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
1281  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
1282  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
1283  if (!fr_cond_assert(fr_value_box_field_sizes[value->type] == min)) return -1;
1284  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, ((uint8_t const *)&value->datum) + fr_value_box_offsets[value->type], min);
1285  break;
1286 
1287  /*
1288  * Needs a bytesex operation
1289  */
1290  case FR_TYPE_UINT16:
1291  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
1292  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
1293  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
1294  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
1295  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
1296  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT32:
1297  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT64:
1298  {
1299  fr_value_box_t tmp;
1300 
1301  if (!fr_cond_assert(fr_value_box_field_sizes[value->type] == min)) return -1;
1302 
1303  fr_value_box_hton(&tmp, value);
1304  fr_dbuff_in_memcpy(dbuff, ((uint8_t const *)&tmp.datum) + fr_value_box_offsets[value->type], min);
1305  }
1306  break;
1307 
1308  /*
1309  * Dates and deltas are stored internally as
1310  * 64-bit nanoseconds. We have to convert to the
1311  * network format. First by resolution (ns, us,
1312  * ms, s), and then by size (16/32/64-bit).
1313  */
1314  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
1315  {
1316  uint64_t date;
1317 
1318  if (!value->enumv) {
1319  goto date_seconds;
1320 
1321  } else switch (value->enumv->flags.type_size) {
1322  date_seconds:
1323  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC:
1324  date = fr_unix_time_to_sec(value->vb_date);
1325  break;
1326 
1327  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
1328  date = fr_unix_time_to_msec(value->vb_date);
1329  break;
1330 
1331  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
1332  date = fr_unix_time_to_usec(value->vb_date);
1333  break;
1334 
1335  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
1336  date = fr_unix_time_to_usec(value->vb_date);
1337  break;
1338 
1339  default:
1340  goto unsupported;
1341  }
1342 
1343  if (!value->enumv) {
1344  goto date_size4;
1345 
1346  } else switch (value->enumv->flags.length) {
1347  case 2:
1348  if (date > UINT16_MAX) date = UINT16_MAX;
1349  fr_dbuff_in(dbuff, (int16_t) date);
1350  break;
1351 
1352  date_size4:
1353  case 4:
1354  if (date > UINT32_MAX) date = UINT32_MAX;
1355  fr_dbuff_in(dbuff, (int32_t) date);
1356  break;
1357 
1358  case 8:
1359  fr_dbuff_in(dbuff, date);
1360  break;
1361 
1362  default:
1363  goto unsupported;
1364  }
1365 
1366  }
1367  break;
1368 
1369  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
1370  {
1371  int64_t date; /* may be negative */
1372 
1373  if (!value->enumv) {
1374  goto delta_seconds;
1375 
1376  } else switch (value->enumv->flags.type_size) {
1377  delta_seconds:
1378  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC:
1379  date = fr_time_delta_to_sec(value->vb_time_delta);
1380  break;
1381 
1382  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
1383  date = fr_time_delta_to_msec(value->vb_time_delta);
1384  break;
1385 
1386  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
1387  date = fr_time_delta_to_usec(value->vb_time_delta);
1388  break;
1389 
1390  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
1391  date = value->vb_time_delta;
1392  break;
1393 
1394  default:
1395  goto unsupported;
1396  }
1397 
1398  if (!value->enumv) {
1399  goto delta_size4;
1400 
1401  } else switch (value->enumv->flags.length) {
1402  case 2:
1403  if (date < INT16_MIN) {
1404  date = INT16_MIN;
1405  } else if (date > INT16_MAX) {
1406  date = INT16_MAX;
1407  }
1408  fr_dbuff_in(dbuff, (int16_t)date);
1409  break;
1410 
1411  delta_size4:
1412  case 4:
1413  if (date < INT32_MIN) {
1414  date = INT32_MIN;
1415  } else if (date > INT32_MAX) {
1416  date = INT32_MAX;
1417  }
1418  fr_dbuff_in(dbuff, (int32_t)date);
1419  break;
1420 
1421  case 8:
1422  fr_dbuff_in(dbuff, (int64_t)date);
1423  break;
1424 
1425  default:
1426  goto unsupported;
1427  }
1428 
1429  }
1430  break;
1431 
1432  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
1433  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
1434  case FR_TYPE_SIZE:
1435  case FR_TYPE_NON_VALUES:
1436  goto unsupported;
1437  }
1438 
1439  if (need) *need = 0;
1440 
1441  return min;
1442 }
1443 
1444 /** Decode a #fr_value_box_t from serialized binary data
1445  *
1446  * The general deserialization rules are:
1447  *
1448  * - Octets are decoded in binary form (not hex).
1449  * - Strings are decoded without the trailing \0 byte. Strings must consist only of valid UTF8 chars.
1450  * - Integers are decoded big-endian.
1451  * - Bools are decoded using one byte, with value 0x00 (false) or 0x01 (true).
1452  * - Signed integers are decoded two's complement, with the MSB as the sign bit.
1453  * Byte order is big-endian.
1454  * - Network addresses are decoded big-endian.
1455  * - IPv4 prefixes are decoded with 1 byte for the prefix, then 4 bytes of address.
1456  * - IPv6 prefixes are decoded with 1 byte for the scope_id, 1 byte for the prefix,
1457  * and 16 bytes of address.
1458  * - Floats are decoded in IEEE-754 format with a big-endian byte order. We rely
1459  * on the fact that the C standards require floats to be represented in IEEE-754
1460  * format in memory.
1461  * - Dates are decoded as 32bit unsigned UNIX timestamps.
1462  *
1463  * @param[in] ctx Where to allocate any talloc buffers required.
1464  * @param[out] dst value_box to write the result to.
1465  * @param[in] type to decode data to.
1466  * @param[in] enumv Aliases for values.
1467  * @param[in] src Binary data to decode.
1468  * @param[in] len Length of data to decode. For fixed length types we only
1469  * decode complete values.
1470  * @param[in] tainted Whether the value came from a trusted source.
1471  * @return
1472  * - >= 0 The number of bytes consumed.
1473  * - <0 - The negative offset where the error occurred.
1474  * - FR_VALUE_BOX_NET_OOM (negative value) - Out of memory.
1475  */
1476 ssize_t fr_value_box_from_network(TALLOC_CTX *ctx,
1477  fr_value_box_t *dst, fr_type_t type, fr_dict_attr_t const *enumv,
1478  uint8_t const *src, size_t len,
1479  bool tainted)
1480 {
1481  uint8_t const *p = src;
1482  uint8_t const *end = p + len;
1483  size_t min, max;
1484 
1485  min = fr_value_box_network_sizes[type][0];
1486  max = fr_value_box_network_sizes[type][1];
1487 
1488  if (len < min) {
1489  fr_strerror_printf("Got truncated value parsing type \"%s\". "
1490  "Expected length >= %zu bytes, got %zu bytes",
1491  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, type, "<INVALID>"),
1492  min, len);
1493  return -(len);
1494  }
1495  if (len > max) {
1496  fr_strerror_printf("Found trailing garbage parsing type \"%s\". "
1497  "Expected length <= %zu bytes, got %zu bytes",
1498  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, type, "<INVALID>"),
1499  max, len);
1500  return -(max);
1501  }
1502 
1503  switch (type) {
1504  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
1505  if (fr_value_box_bstrndup(ctx, dst, enumv, (char const *)src, len, tainted) < 0) {
1506  return FR_VALUE_BOX_NET_OOM;
1507  }
1508  return len;
1509 
1510  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
1511  if (fr_value_box_memdup(ctx, dst, enumv, src, len, tainted) < 0) return FR_VALUE_BOX_NET_OOM;
1512  return len;
1513  default:
1514  break;
1515  }
1516 
1517  /*
1518  * Pre-Initialise box for non-variable types
1519  */
1520  fr_value_box_init(dst, type, enumv, tainted);
1521  switch (type) {
1522  /*
1523  * Already in network byte order
1524  */
1525  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
1526  dst->vb_ip = (fr_ipaddr_t){
1527  .af = AF_INET,
1528  .prefix = 32,
1529  };
1530  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, p, (end - p));
1531  break;
1532 
1533  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
1534  dst->vb_ip = (fr_ipaddr_t){
1535  .af = AF_INET,
1536  .prefix = *p++,
1537  };
1538  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, p, (end - p));
1539  break;
1540 
1541  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
1542  dst->vb_ip = (fr_ipaddr_t){
1543  .af = AF_INET6,
1544  .scope_id = len == max ? *p++ : 0, /* optional */
1545  .prefix = 128
1546  };
1547  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v6, p, (end - p));
1548  break;
1549 
1550  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
1551  dst->vb_ip = (fr_ipaddr_t){
1552  .af = AF_INET6,
1553  .scope_id = len == max ? *p++ : 0,
1554  };
1555 
1556  /*
1557  * Can't increment p multiple times
1558  * in an initialiser because the operations
1559  * aren't explicitly ordered.
1560  */
1561  dst->vb_ip.prefix = *p++;
1562  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v6, p, (end - p));
1563  break;
1564 
1565  case FR_TYPE_BOOL:
1566  dst->datum.boolean = src[0] > 0 ? true : false;
1567  break;
1568 
1569  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
1570  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
1571  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
1572  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
1573  memcpy(((uint8_t *)&dst->datum) + fr_value_box_offsets[type], src, len);
1574  break;
1575 
1576  /*
1577  * Needs a bytesex operation
1578  */
1579  case FR_TYPE_UINT16:
1580  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
1581  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
1582  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
1583  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
1584  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
1585  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT32:
1586  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT64:
1587  memcpy(((uint8_t *)&dst->datum) + fr_value_box_offsets[type], src, len);
1588  fr_value_box_hton(dst, dst); /* Operate in-place */
1589  break;
1590 
1591  /*
1592  * Dates and deltas are stored internally as
1593  * 64-bit nanoseconds. We have to convert from
1594  * the network format. First by size
1595  * (16/32/64-bit), and then by resolution (ns,
1596  * us, ms, s).
1597  */
1598  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
1599  {
1600  size_t i, length = 4;
1601  fr_time_res_t precision = FR_TIME_RES_SEC;
1602  uint64_t date;
1603 
1604  if (enumv) {
1605  length = enumv->flags.length;
1606  precision = (fr_time_res_t)enumv->flags.type_size;
1607  }
1608 
1609  /*
1610  * Input data doesn't match what we were told we
1611  * need.
1612  */
1613  if (len != length) return (len > length) ? -(length) : -(len);
1614 
1615  /*
1616  * Just loop over the input data until we reach
1617  * the end. Shifting it every time.
1618  */
1619  date = 0;
1620  dst->enumv = enumv;
1621 
1622  i = 0;
1623  do {
1624  date <<= 8;
1625  date |= *(p++);
1626  i++;
1627  } while (i < length);
1628 
1629  switch (precision) {
1630  default:
1631  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC: /* external seconds, internal nanoseconds */
1632  date *= NSEC;
1633  break;
1634 
1635  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
1636  date *= 1000000;
1637  break;
1638 
1639  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
1640  date *= 1000;
1641  break;
1642 
1643  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
1644  break;
1645  }
1646 
1647  dst->vb_date = date;
1648  }
1649  break;
1650 
1651  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
1652  {
1653  size_t i, length = 4;
1654  fr_time_res_t precision = FR_TIME_RES_SEC;
1655  uint64_t date;
1656 
1657  if (enumv) {
1658  length = enumv->flags.length;
1659  precision = (fr_time_res_t)enumv->flags.type_size;
1660  }
1661 
1662  /*
1663  * Input data doesn't match what we were told we
1664  * need.
1665  */
1666  if (len != length) return (len > length) ? -(length) : -(len);
1667 
1668  /*
1669  * Just loop over the input data until we reach
1670  * the end. Shifting it every time.
1671  */
1672  date = 0;
1673  dst->enumv = enumv;
1674 
1675  i = 0;
1676  do {
1677  date <<= 8;
1678  date |= *(p++);
1679  i++;
1680  } while (i < length);
1681 
1682  switch (precision) {
1683  default:
1684  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC: /* external seconds, internal nanoseconds */
1685  dst->vb_time_delta = fr_time_delta_from_sec(date);
1686  break;
1687 
1688  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
1689  dst->vb_time_delta = fr_time_delta_from_msec(date);
1690  break;
1691 
1692  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
1693  dst->vb_time_delta = fr_time_delta_from_usec(date);
1694  break;
1695 
1696  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
1697  dst->vb_time_delta = date;
1698  break;
1699  }
1700 
1701  }
1702  break;
1703 
1704  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
1705  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
1706  break; /* Already dealt with */
1707 
1708  case FR_TYPE_SIZE:
1709  case FR_TYPE_NON_VALUES:
1710  fr_strerror_printf("Cannot decode type \"%s\" - Is not a value",
1711  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, type, "<INVALID>"));
1712  break;
1713  }
1714 
1715  return len;
1716 }

1718 /** Convert octets to a fixed size value box value
1719  *
1720  * All fixed size types are allowed.
1721  *
1722  * @param dst Where to write result of casting.
1723  * @param dst_type to cast to.
1724  * @param dst_enumv enumeration values.
1725  * @param src Input data.
1726  */
1727 static int fr_value_box_fixed_size_from_octets(fr_value_box_t *dst,
1728  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
1729  fr_value_box_t const *src)
1730 {
1731  switch (dst_type) {
1732  case FR_TYPE_FIXED_SIZE:
1733  break;
1734 
1735  default:
1736  if (!fr_cond_assert(false)) return -1;
1737  }
1738 
1739  if (src->vb_length < fr_value_box_network_sizes[dst_type][0]) {
1740  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Source is length %zd is smaller than "
1741  "destination type size %zd",
1742  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
1743  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
1744  src->vb_length,
1745  fr_value_box_network_sizes[dst_type][0]);
1746  return -1;
1747  }
1748 
1749  if (src->vb_length > fr_value_box_network_sizes[dst_type][1]) {
1750  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Source length %zd is greater than "
1751  "destination type size %zd",
1752  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
1753  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
1754  src->vb_length,
1755  fr_value_box_network_sizes[dst_type][1]);
1756  return -1;
1757  }
1758 
1759  fr_value_box_init(dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src->tainted);
1760 
1761  /*
1762  * Copy the raw octets into the datum of a value_box
1763  * inverting bytesex for uint32s (if LE).
1764  */
1765  memcpy(&dst->datum, src->vb_octets, fr_value_box_field_sizes[dst_type]);
1766  fr_value_box_hton(dst, dst);
1767 
1768  return 0;
1769 }

1779 /** Convert any supported type to a string
1780  *
1781  * All non-structural types are allowed.
1782  *
1783  * @param ctx unused.
1784  * @param dst Where to write result of casting.
1785  * @param dst_type to cast to.
1786  * @param dst_enumv enumeration values.
1787  * @param src Input data.
1788  */
1789 static inline int fr_value_box_cast_to_strvalue(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t *dst,
1790  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
1791  fr_value_box_t const *src)
1792 {
1793  if (!fr_cond_assert(dst_type == FR_TYPE_STRING)) return -1;
1794 
1795  switch (src->type) {
1796  /*
1797  * The presentation format of octets is hex
1798  * What we actually want here is the raw string
1799  */
1800  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
1801  return fr_value_box_bstrndup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv,
1802  (char const *)src->vb_octets, src->vb_length, src->tainted);
1803 
1804  case FR_TYPE_GROUP:
1805  {
1806  fr_cursor_t cursor;
1807  fr_value_box_t *vb;
1808 
1809  /*
1810  * Initialise an empty buffer we can
1811  * append to.
1812  */
1813  if (fr_value_box_bstrndup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv, NULL, 0, src->tainted) < 0) return -1;
1814 
1815  for (vb = fr_cursor_init(&cursor, &src->vb_group);
1816  vb;
1817  vb = fr_cursor_next(&cursor)) {
1818  /*
1819  * Attempt to cast to a string so
1820  * we can append.
1821  */
1822  if (vb->type != FR_TYPE_STRING) {
1823  fr_value_box_t tmp;
1824  int ret;
1825 
1826  if (fr_value_box_cast(ctx, &tmp, FR_TYPE_STRING, NULL, vb) < 0) return -1;
1827 
1828  /*
1829  * Append and continue
1830  */
1831  ret = fr_value_box_bstr_append_buffer(ctx, dst, tmp.vb_strvalue, tmp.tainted);
1832  fr_value_box_clear(&tmp);
1833  if (ret < 0) {
1834  error:
1835  fr_value_box_clear(dst);
1836  return -1;
1837  }
1838  continue;
1839  }
1840 
1841  if (fr_value_box_bstr_append_buffer(ctx, dst, vb->vb_strvalue, vb->tainted) < 0) goto error;
1842  }
1843  }
1844  return 0;
1845 
1846  /*
1847  * Get the presentation format
1848  */
1849  default:
1850  {
1851  char *str;
1852 
1853  fr_value_box_aprint(ctx, &str, src, NULL);
1854  if (unlikely(!str)) return -1;
1855 
1856  return fr_value_box_bstrdup_buffer_shallow(NULL, dst, dst_enumv, str, src->tainted);
1857  }
1858  }
1859 }

1861 /** Convert any supported type to octets
1862  *
1863  * All non-structural types are allowed.
1864  *
1865  * @param ctx unused.
1866  * @param dst Where to write result of casting.
1867  * @param dst_type to cast to.
1868  * @param dst_enumv enumeration values.
1869  * @param src Input data.
1870  */
1871 static inline int fr_value_box_cast_to_octets(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t *dst,
1872  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
1873  fr_value_box_t const *src)
1874 {
1875  if (!fr_cond_assert(dst_type == FR_TYPE_OCTETS)) return -1;
1876 
1877  switch (src->type) {
1878  /*
1879  * <string> (excluding terminating \0)
1880  */
1881  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
1882  if (fr_value_box_memdup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv,
1883  (uint8_t const *)src->vb_strvalue, src->vb_length, src->tainted) < 0) {
1884  return -1;
1885  }
1886  return 0;
1887 
1888  case FR_TYPE_GROUP:
1889  {
1890  fr_cursor_t cursor;
1891  fr_value_box_t *vb;
1892 
1893  /*
1894  * Initialise an empty buffer we can
1895  * append to.
1896  */
1897  if (fr_value_box_memdup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv, NULL, 0, src->tainted) < 0) return -1;
1898 
1899  for (vb = fr_cursor_init(&cursor, &src->vb_group);
1900  vb;
1901  vb = fr_cursor_next(&cursor)) {
1902  /*
1903  * Attempt to cast to octets so
1904  * we can append;
1905  */
1906  if (vb->type != FR_TYPE_OCTETS) {
1907  fr_value_box_t tmp;
1908  int ret;
1909 
1910  if (fr_value_box_cast(ctx, &tmp, FR_TYPE_OCTETS, NULL, vb) < 0) return -1;
1911 
1912  /*
1913  * Append and continue
1914  */
1915  ret = fr_value_box_mem_append_buffer(ctx, dst, tmp.vb_octets, tmp.tainted);
1916  fr_value_box_clear(&tmp);
1917  if (ret < 0) {
1918  error:
1919  fr_value_box_clear(dst);
1920  return -1;
1921  }
1922  continue;
1923  }
1924 
1925  if (fr_value_box_mem_append_buffer(ctx, dst, vb->vb_octets, vb->tainted) < 0) goto error;
1926  }
1927  return 0;
1928  }
1929 
1930  /*
1931  * <4 bytes address>
1932  */
1933  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
1934  return fr_value_box_memdup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv,
1935  (uint8_t const *)&src->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr,
1936  sizeof(src->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr), src->tainted);
1937 
1938  /*
1939  * <1 uint8 prefix> + <4 bytes address>
1940  */
1941  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
1942  {
1943  uint8_t *bin;
1944 
1945  if (fr_value_box_mem_alloc(ctx, &bin, dst, dst_enumv,
1946  sizeof(src->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr) + 1, src->tainted) < 0) return -1;
1947 
1948  bin[0] = src->vb_ip.prefix;
1949  memcpy(&bin[1], (uint8_t const *)&src->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr, sizeof(src->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
1950  }
1951  return 0;
1952 
1953  /*
1954  * <16 bytes address>
1955  */
1956  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
1957  return fr_value_box_memdup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv,
1958  (uint8_t const *)src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr,
1959  sizeof(src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr), src->tainted);
1960 
1961  /*
1962  * <1 uint8 prefix> + <1 uint8 scope> + <16 bytes address>
1963  */
1964  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
1965  {
1966  uint8_t *bin;
1967 
1968  if (fr_value_box_mem_alloc(ctx, &bin, dst, dst_enumv,
1969  sizeof(src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr) + 2, src->tainted) < 0) return -1;
1970  bin[0] = src->vb_ip.scope_id;
1971  bin[1] = src->vb_ip.prefix;
1972  memcpy(&bin[2], src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, sizeof(src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr));
1973  }
1974  return 0;
1975 
1976  /*
1977  * Get the raw binary in memory representation
1978  */
1979  case FR_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1980  {
1981  fr_value_box_t tmp;
1982 
1983  fr_value_box_hton(&tmp, src); /* Flip any numeric representations */
1984  return fr_value_box_memdup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv,
1985  ((uint8_t const *)&tmp.datum) + fr_value_box_offsets[src->type],
1986  fr_value_box_field_sizes[src->type], src->tainted);
1987  }
1988 
1989  default:
1990  /* Not the same talloc_memdup call as above. The above memdup reads data from the dst */
1991  return fr_value_box_memdup(ctx, dst, dst_enumv,
1992  ((uint8_t const *)&src->datum) + fr_value_box_offsets[src->type],
1993  fr_value_box_field_sizes[src->type], src->tainted);
1994  }
1995 }

1997 /** Convert any supported type to an IPv4 address
1998  *
1999  * Allowed input types are:
2000  * - FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR (with v4 prefix).
2001  * - FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX (with 32bit mask).
2002  * - FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX (with v4 prefix and 128bit mask).
2003  * - FR_TYPE_OCTETS (of length 4).
2004  * - FR_TYPE_UINT32
2005  *
2006  * @param ctx unused.
2007  * @param dst Where to write result of casting.
2008  * @param dst_type to cast to.
2009  * @param dst_enumv enumeration values.
2010  * @param src Input data.
2011  */
2012 static inline int fr_value_box_cast_to_ipv4addr(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t *dst,
2013  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
2014  fr_value_box_t const *src)
2015 {
2016  fr_assert(dst_type == FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR);
2017 
2018  switch (src->type) {
2019  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
2020  return fr_value_box_from_str(ctx, dst, &dst_type, dst_enumv,
2021  src->vb_strvalue, src->vb_length, '\0', src->tainted);
2022 
2023  default:
2024  break;
2025  }
2026 
2027  /*
2028  * Pre-initialise box for non-variable types
2029  */
2030  fr_value_box_init(dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src->tainted);
2031  dst->vb_ip.af = AF_INET;
2032  dst->vb_ip.prefix = 32;
2033  dst->vb_ip.scope_id = 0;
2034 
2035  switch (src->type) {
2036  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
2037  if (memcmp(src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, v4_v6_map, sizeof(v4_v6_map)) != 0) {
2038  bad_v6_prefix_map:
2039  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. No IPv4-IPv6 mapping prefix",
2040  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2041  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2042  return -1;
2043  }
2044 
2045  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, &src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr[sizeof(v4_v6_map)],
2046  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4));
2047 
2048  break;
2049 
2050  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
2051  if (src->vb_ip.prefix != 32) {
2052  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Only /32 (not %i/) prefixes may be "
2053  "cast to IP address types",
2054  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2055  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2056  src->vb_ip.prefix);
2057  return -1;
2058  }
2059  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, &src->vb_ip.addr.v4, sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4));
2060  break;
2061 
2062  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
2063  if (src->vb_ip.prefix != 128) {
2064  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Only /128 (not /%i) prefixes may be "
2065  "cast to IP address types",
2066  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2067  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2068  src->vb_ip.prefix);
2069  return -1;
2070  }
2071  if (memcmp(&src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, v4_v6_map, sizeof(v4_v6_map)) != 0) goto bad_v6_prefix_map;
2072  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, &src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr[sizeof(v4_v6_map)],
2073  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4));
2074  break;
2075 
2076  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
2077  if (src->vb_length != sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr)) {
2078  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Needed octet string of length %zu, got %zu",
2079  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2080  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2081  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr), src->vb_length);
2082  return -1;
2083  }
2084  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, src->vb_octets, sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
2085  break;
2086 
2087  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
2088  {
2089  uint32_t net;
2090 
2091  net = ntohl(src->vb_uint32);
2092  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, (uint8_t *)&net, sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
2093  }
2094  break;
2095 
2096  default:
2097  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Unsupported",
2098  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2099  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2100  return -1;
2101  }
2102 
2103  return 0;
2104 }

2106 /** Convert any supported type to an IPv6 address
2107  *
2108  * Allowed input types are:
2109  * - FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR
2110  * - FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX (with 32bit mask).
2111  * - FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX (with 128bit mask).
2112  * - FR_TYPE_OCTETS (of length 16).
2113  *
2114  * @param ctx unused.
2115  * @param dst Where to write result of casting.
2116  * @param dst_type to cast to.
2117  * @param dst_enumv enumeration values.
2118  * @param src Input data.
2119  */
2120 static inline int fr_value_box_cast_to_ipv4prefix(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t *dst,
2121  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
2122  fr_value_box_t const *src)
2123 {
2124  fr_assert(dst_type == FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX);
2125 
2126  switch (src->type) {
2127  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
2128  return fr_value_box_from_str(ctx, dst, &dst_type, dst_enumv,
2129  src->vb_strvalue, src->vb_length, '\0', src->tainted);
2130 
2131  default:
2132  break;
2133  }
2134 
2135  /*
2136  * Pre-initialise box for non-variable types
2137  */
2138  fr_value_box_init(dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src->tainted);
2139  dst->vb_ip.af = AF_INET;
2140  dst->vb_ip.scope_id = 0;
2141 
2142  switch (src->type) {
2143  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
2144  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip, &src->vb_ip, sizeof(dst->vb_ip));
2145  break;
2146 
2147  /*
2148  * Copy the last four bytes, to make an IPv4prefix
2149  */
2150  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
2151  if (memcmp(src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, v4_v6_map, sizeof(v4_v6_map)) != 0) {
2152  bad_v6_prefix_map:
2153  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. No IPv4-IPv6 mapping prefix",
2154  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2155  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2156  return -1;
2157  }
2158  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr, &src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr[sizeof(v4_v6_map)],
2159  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
2160  dst->vb_ip.prefix = 32;
2161  break;
2162 
2163  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
2164  if (memcmp(src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, v4_v6_map, sizeof(v4_v6_map)) != 0) goto bad_v6_prefix_map;
2165 
2166  if (src->vb_ip.prefix < (sizeof(v4_v6_map) << 3)) {
2167  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Expected prefix >= %u bits got %u bits",
2168  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2169  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2170  (unsigned int)(sizeof(v4_v6_map) << 3), src->vb_ip.prefix);
2171  return -1;
2172  }
2173  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr, &src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr[sizeof(v4_v6_map)],
2174  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
2175 
2176  /*
2177  * Subtract the bits used by the v4_v6_map to get the v4 prefix bits
2178  */
2179  dst->vb_ip.prefix = src->vb_ip.prefix - (sizeof(v4_v6_map) << 3);
2180  break;
2181 
2182  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
2183  if (src->vb_length != sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr) + 1) {
2184  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Needed octet string of length %zu, got %zu",
2185  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2186  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2187  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr) + 1, src->vb_length);
2188  return -1;
2189  }
2190  dst->vb_ip.prefix = src->vb_octets[0];
2191  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, &src->vb_octets[1], sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
2192  break;
2193 
2194  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
2195  {
2196  uint32_t net;
2197 
2198  net = ntohl(src->vb_uint32);
2199  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v4, (uint8_t *)&net, sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v4.s_addr));
2200  dst->vb_ip.prefix = 32;
2201  break;
2202  }
2203 
2204  default:
2205  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Unsupported",
2206  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2207  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2208  return -1;
2209  }
2210 
2211  return 0;
2212 }

2385  memcpy(dst->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, src->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr,
2386  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr));
2387  dst->vb_ip.prefix = 128;
2388  dst->vb_ip.scope_id = src->vb_ip.scope_id;
2389  break;
2390 
2391  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
2392  if (src->vb_length != (sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr) + 2)) {
2393  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Needed octet string of length %zu, got %zu",
2394  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2395  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2396  sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr) + 2, src->vb_length);
2397  return -1;
2398  }
2399  dst->vb_ip.scope_id = src->vb_octets[0];
2400  dst->vb_ip.prefix = src->vb_octets[1];
2401  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr, src->vb_octets, sizeof(dst->vb_ip.addr.v6.s6_addr));
2402  break;
2403 
2404  default:
2405  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Unsupported",
2406  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2407  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2408  return -1;
2409  }
2410  return 0;
2411 }

2551 /** Convert any signed or unsigned integer type to any other signed or unsigned integer type
2552  *
2553  */
2554 static inline int fr_value_box_cast_integer_to_integer(UNUSED TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t *dst,
2555  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
2556  fr_value_box_t const *src)
2557 {
2558  uint64_t tmp = 0;
2559  size_t len = fr_value_box_field_sizes[src->type];
2560  int64_t min;
2561 
2562 #define SIGN_BIT_HIGH(_int, _len) ((((uint64_t)1) << ((_len << 3) - 1)) & _int)
2563 #define SIGN_PROMOTE(_int, _len) ((_len) < sizeof(_int) ? \
2564  (_int) | (~((__typeof__(_int))0)) << ((_len) << 3) : (_int))
2565 
2566  switch (src->type) {
2567  /*
2568  * Dates are always represented in nanoseconds
2569  * internally, but when we convert to another
2570  * integer type, we scale appropriately.
2571  *
2572  * i.e. if the attribute value resolution is
2573  * seconds, then the integer value is
2574  * nanoseconds -> seconds.
2575  */
2576  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
2577  if (dst->enumv) {
2578  switch (dst->enumv->flags.type_size) {
2579  date_src_seconds:
2580  default:
2581  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC:
2582  tmp = fr_unix_time_to_sec(src->vb_date);
2583  break;
2584 
2585  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
2586  tmp = fr_unix_time_to_usec(src->vb_date);
2587  break;
2588 
2589  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
2590  tmp = fr_unix_time_to_msec(src->vb_date);
2591  break;
2592 
2593  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
2594  tmp = src->vb_date;
2595  break;
2596  }
2597  } else goto date_src_seconds;
2598  break;
2599 
2600  /*
2601  * Same deal with time deltas. Note that
2602  * even though we store the value as an
2603  * unsigned integer, it'll be cast to a
2604  * signed integer for comparisons.
2605  */
2606  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
2607  if (dst->enumv) {
2608  switch (dst->enumv->flags.type_size) {
2609  delta_src_seconds:
2610  default:
2611  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC:
2612  tmp = (uint64_t)fr_time_delta_to_sec(src->vb_time_delta);
2613  break;
2614 
2615  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
2616  tmp = (uint64_t)fr_time_delta_to_usec(src->vb_time_delta);
2617  break;
2618 
2619  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
2620  tmp = (uint64_t)fr_time_delta_to_msec(src->vb_time_delta);
2621  break;
2622 
2623  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
2624  tmp = (uint64_t)src->vb_time_delta;
2625  break;
2626  }
2627  } else goto delta_src_seconds;
2628  break;
2629 
2630  default:
2631 #ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
2632  memcpy(((uint8_t *)&tmp) + (sizeof(tmp) - len),
2633  ((uint8_t const *)src) + fr_value_box_offsets[src->type], len);
2634 #else
2635  memcpy(&tmp, src, len);
2636 #endif
2637  break;
2638  }
2639 
2640  min = fr_value_box_integer_min[dst_type];
2641  if ((min < 0) && SIGN_BIT_HIGH(tmp, len)) {
2642  tmp = SIGN_PROMOTE(tmp, len);
2643  if (((int64_t)tmp < min)) {
2644  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. %"PRId64" "
2645  "outside value range %"PRId64"-%"PRIu64,
2646  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2647  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2648  (int64_t)tmp,
2649  min, fr_value_box_integer_max[dst_type]);
2650  return -1;
2651  }
2652  } else if (tmp > fr_value_box_integer_max[dst_type]) {
2653  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. %"PRIu64" "
2654  "outside value range 0-%"PRIu64,
2655  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2656  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2657  tmp, fr_value_box_integer_max[dst_type]);
2658  return -1;
2659  }
2660 
2661  fr_value_box_init(dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src->tainted);
2662  switch (dst_type) {
2663  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
2664  if (dst->enumv) {
2665  switch (dst->enumv->flags.type_size) {
2666  date_dst_seconds:
2667  default:
2668  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC:
2669  dst->vb_date = fr_unix_time_from_sec((fr_unix_time_t)tmp);
2670  break;
2671 
2672  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
2673  dst->vb_date = fr_unix_time_from_usec((fr_unix_time_t)tmp);
2674  break;
2675 
2676  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
2677  dst->vb_date = fr_unix_time_from_msec((fr_unix_time_t)tmp);
2678  break;
2679 
2680  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
2681  dst->vb_date = fr_unix_time_from_nsec((fr_unix_time_t)tmp);
2682  break;
2683  }
2684  } else goto date_dst_seconds;
2685  break;
2686 
2687  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
2688  if (dst->enumv) {
2689  switch (dst->enumv->flags.type_size) {
2690  delta_dst_seconds:
2691  default:
2692  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC:
2693  dst->vb_time_delta = fr_time_delta_from_sec((fr_time_delta_t)tmp);
2694  break;
2695 
2696  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
2697  dst->vb_time_delta = fr_time_delta_from_usec((fr_time_delta_t)tmp);
2698  break;
2699 
2700  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
2701  dst->vb_time_delta = fr_time_delta_from_msec((fr_time_delta_t)tmp);
2702  break;
2703 
2704  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
2705  dst->vb_time_delta = fr_time_delta_from_nsec((fr_time_delta_t)tmp);
2706  break;
2707  }
2708  } else goto delta_dst_seconds;
2709  break;
2710 
2711  default:
2712 #ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
2713  memcpy(((uint8_t *)dst) + fr_value_box_offsets[dst_type],
2714  ((uint8_t *)&tmp) + (sizeof(tmp) - len), fr_value_box_field_sizes[dst_type]);
2715 #else
2716  memcpy(((uint8_t *)dst) + fr_value_box_offsets[dst_type],
2717  &tmp, fr_value_box_field_sizes[dst_type]);
2718 #endif
2719  break;
2720  }
2721 
2722  return 0;
2723 }

2725 /** Convert any value to a signed or unsigned integer
2726  *
2727  * @param ctx unused.
2728  * @param dst Where to write result of casting.
2729  * @param dst_type to cast to.
2730  * @param dst_enumv enumeration values.
2731  * @param src Input data.
2732  */
2733 static inline int fr_value_box_cast_to_integer(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t *dst,
2734  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
2735  fr_value_box_t const *src)
2736 {
2737  switch (src->type) {
2738  default:
2739  bad_cast:
2740  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Unsupported",
2741  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2742  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2743  return -1;
2744 
2745  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
2746  return fr_value_box_from_str(ctx, dst, &dst_type, dst_enumv,
2747  src->vb_strvalue, src->vb_length, '\0', src->tainted);
2748 
2749  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
2750  return fr_value_box_fixed_size_from_octets(dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2751 
2752  case FR_TYPE_INTEGER:
2753  return fr_value_box_cast_integer_to_integer(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2754 
2755  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
2756  {
2757  fr_value_box_t tmp;
2758 
2759  switch (dst_type) {
2760  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
2761  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
2762  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
2763  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
2764  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
2765  break;
2766 
2767  default:
2768  goto bad_cast;
2769  }
2770 
2771  fr_value_box_init(&tmp, FR_TYPE_UINT32, src->enumv, src->tainted);
2772  memcpy(&tmp.vb_uint32, &src->vb_ip.addr.v4, sizeof(tmp.vb_uint32));
2773  fr_value_box_hton(&tmp, &tmp);
2774  return fr_value_box_cast_integer_to_integer(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, &tmp);
2775  }
2776 
2777  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
2778  {
2779  fr_value_box_t tmp;
2780 
2781  switch (dst_type) {
2782  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
2783  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
2784  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
2785  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
2786  break;
2787 
2788  default:
2789  goto bad_cast;
2790  }
2791 
2792  fr_value_box_init(&tmp, FR_TYPE_UINT64, src->enumv, src->tainted);
2793 #ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
2794  memcpy(((uint8_t *)&tmp.vb_uint64) + (sizeof(tmp.vb_uint64) - sizeof(src->vb_ether)),
2795  &src->vb_ether, sizeof(src->vb_ether));
2796 #else
2797  memcpy(&tmp.vb_uint64, &src->vb_ether, sizeof(tmp.vb_ether));
2798 #endif
2799  fr_value_box_hton(&tmp, &tmp);
2800  return fr_value_box_cast_integer_to_integer(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, &tmp);
2801  }
2802 
2803  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
2804  {
2805  switch (dst_type) {
2806  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
2807  break;
2808 
2809  default:
2810  goto bad_cast;
2811  }
2812 
2813  fr_value_box_init(dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src->tainted);
2814  dst->vb_uint64 = fr_net_to_uint64(&src->vb_ifid[0]);
2815  return 0;
2816  }
2817  }
2818 
2819  return 0;
2820 }

2822 /** Convert one type of fr_value_box_t to another
2823  *
2824  * This should be the canonical function used to convert between INTERNAL data formats.
2825  *
2826  * If you want to convert from PRESENTATION format, use #fr_value_box_from_str.
2827  *
2828  * @note src and dst must not be the same box. We do not support casting in place.
2829  *
2830  * @param ctx to allocate buffers in (usually the same as dst)
2831  * @param dst Where to write result of casting.
2832  * @param dst_type to cast to.
2833  * @param dst_enumv Aliases for values contained within this fr_value_box_t.
2834  * If #fr_value_box_t is passed to #fr_value_box_aprint
2835  * names will be printed instead of actual value.
2836  * @param src Input data.
2837  * @return
2838  * - 0 on success.
2839  * - -1 on failure.
2840  */
2841 int fr_value_box_cast(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t *dst,
2842  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv,
2843  fr_value_box_t const *src)
2844 {
2845  if (!fr_cond_assert(dst_type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
2846  if (!fr_cond_assert(src != dst)) return -1;
2847  if (!fr_cond_assert(src->type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
2848 
2849  if (fr_dict_non_data_types[dst_type]) {
2850  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Can only cast simple data types",
2851  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2852  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2853  return -1;
2854  }
2855 
2856  /*
2857  * If it's the same type, copy, but set the enumv
2858  * in the destination box to be the one provided.
2859  *
2860  * The theory here is that the attribute value isn't
2861  * being converted into its presentation format and
2862  * re-parsed, and the enumv names only get applied
2863  * when converting internal values to/from strings,
2864  * so it's OK just to swap out the enumv.
2865  *
2866  * If there's a compelling case in the future we
2867  * might revisit this, but it'd likely mean fixing
2868  * all the casting functions to treat any value
2869  * with an enumv as a string, which seems weird.
2870  */
2871  if (dst_type == src->type) {
2872  int ret;
2873 
2874  ret = fr_value_box_copy(ctx, dst, src);
2875  if (ret < 0) return ret;
2876 
2877  dst->enumv = dst_enumv;
2878 
2879  return ret;
2880  }
2881 
2882  /*
2883  * Initialise dst
2884  */
2885  memset(dst, 0, sizeof(*dst));
2886 
2887  /*
2888  * Dispatch to specialised cast functions
2889  */
2890  switch (dst_type) {
2891  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
2892  return fr_value_box_cast_to_strvalue(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2893 
2894  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
2895  return fr_value_box_cast_to_octets(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2896 
2897  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
2898  return fr_value_box_cast_to_ipv4addr(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2899 
2900  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
2901  return fr_value_box_cast_to_ipv4prefix(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2902 
2903  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
2904  return fr_value_box_cast_to_ipv6addr(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2905 
2906  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
2907  return fr_value_box_cast_to_ipv6prefix(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2908 
2909  /*
2910  * Need func
2911  */
2912  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
2913  case FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_ADDR:
2914  case FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_PREFIX:
2915  break;
2916 
2917  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
2918  return fr_value_box_cast_to_ethernet(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2919 
2920  case FR_TYPE_BOOL:
2921  return fr_value_box_cast_to_bool(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2922 
2923  case FR_TYPE_INTEGER_EXCEPT_BOOL:
2924  return fr_value_box_cast_to_integer(ctx, dst, dst_type, dst_enumv, src);
2925 
2926  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT32:
2927  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT64:
2928  break;
2929 
2930  /*
2931  * Invalid types for casting (should have been caught earlier)
2932  */
2933  case FR_TYPE_VALUE_BOX:
2934  case FR_TYPE_STRUCTURAL:
2935  case FR_TYPE_INVALID:
2936  case FR_TYPE_MAX:
2937  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Invalid destination type",
2938  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2939  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
2940  return -1;
2941  }
2942 
2943  /*
2944  * Deserialise a fr_value_box_t
2945  */
2946  if (src->type == FR_TYPE_STRING) return fr_value_box_from_str(ctx, dst, &dst_type, dst_enumv,
2947  src->vb_strvalue,
2948  src->vb_length, '\0', src->tainted);
2949 
2950  if (src->type == FR_TYPE_OCTETS) {
2951  fr_value_box_t tmp;
2952 
2953  if (src->vb_length < fr_value_box_network_sizes[dst_type][0]) {
2954  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid cast from %s to %s. Source is length %zd is smaller than "
2955  "destination type size %zd",
2956  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, src->type, "<INVALID>"),
2957  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"),
2958  src->vb_length,

3012  fr_type_t dst_type, fr_dict_attr_t const *dst_enumv)

3017  * Simple case, destination type and current
3018  * type are the same.
3019  */
3020  if (vb->type == dst_type) {
3021  vb->enumv = dst_enumv; /* Update the enumv as this may be different */
3022  return 0;

3102 /** Clear/free any existing value
3103  *
3104  * @note Do not use on uninitialised memory.
3105  *
3106  * @param[in] data to clear.
3107  */
3108 inline void fr_value_box_clear_value(fr_value_box_t *data)
3109 {
3110  switch (data->type) {
3111  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
3112  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
3113  talloc_free(data->datum.ptr);
3114  break;
3115 
3116  case FR_TYPE_STRUCTURAL:
3117  /*
3118  * Depth first freeing of children
3119  *
3120  * This ensures orderly freeing, regardless
3121  * of talloc hierarchy.
3122  */
3123  switch (data->datum.children.type) {
3124  case FR_VALUE_BOX_LIST_SINGLE:

3132  fr_value_box_clear_value(vb);
3133  talloc_free(vb);
3134  }

3136  break;

3140  fr_value_box_t *vb = NULL;
3141 
3142  while ((vb = fr_dlist_next(&data->datum.children.dlist, vb))) {
3143  fr_value_box_clear_value(vb);
3144  talloc_free(vb);
3145  }
3146  }
3147  break;

3149  return;
3150

3152  return;
3153 
3154  default:
3155  break;
3156  }
3157

3763

3999 /** Convert integer encoded as string to a fr_value_box_t type
4000  *
4001  * @param[out] dst where to write parsed value.
4002  * @param[in] dst_type type of integer to convert string to.
4003  * @param[in] in String to convert to integer.
4004  * @return
4005  * - 0 on success.
4006  * - -1 on parse error.
4007  */
4008 static int fr_value_box_from_integer_str(fr_value_box_t *dst, fr_type_t dst_type, char const *in)
4009 {
4010  uint64_t uinteger = 0;
4011  int64_t sinteger = 0;
4012  char *p = NULL;
4013 
4014  switch (dst_type) {
4015  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
4016  case FR_TYPE_UINT16:
4017  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
4018  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
4019  fr_skip_whitespace(in);
4020 
4021  if (*in == '-') {
4022  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid negative value \"%s\" for unsigned integer", in);
4023  return -1;
4024  }
4025 
4026  /*
4027  * fr_strtoull checks for overflows and calls
4028  * fr_strerror_printf to set an error.
4029  */
4030  if (fr_strtoull(&uinteger, &p, in) < 0) return -1;
4031  if (*p != '\0') {
4032  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid integer value \"%s\"", in);
4033 
4034  return -1;
4035  }
4036  if (errno == ERANGE) {
4037 
4038 
4039  return -1;
4040  }
4041  break;
4042 
4043  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
4044  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
4045  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
4046  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
4047  /*
4048  * fr_strtoll checks for overflows and calls
4049  * fr_strerror_printf to set an error.
4050  */
4051  if (fr_strtoll(&sinteger, &p, in) < 0) return -1;
4052  if (*p != '\0') {
4053  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid integer value \"%s\"", in);
4054 
4055  return -1;
4056  }
4057  break;
4058 
4059  default:
4060  fr_assert_fail(NULL);
4061  return -1;
4062  }
4063 
4064 #define IN_RANGE_UNSIGNED(_type) \
4065  do { \
4066  if (uinteger > _type ## _MAX) { \
4067  fr_strerror_printf("Value %" PRIu64 " is invalid for type %s (must be in range " \
4068  "0...%" PRIu64 ")", \
4069  uinteger, fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"), \
4070  (uint64_t) _type ## _MAX); \
4071  return -1; \
4072  } \
4073  } while (0)
4074 
4075 #define IN_RANGE_SIGNED(_type) \
4076  do { \
4077  if ((sinteger > _type ## _MAX) || (sinteger < _type ## _MIN)) { \
4078  fr_strerror_printf("Value %" PRId64 " is invalid for type %s (must be in range " \
4079  "%" PRId64 "...%" PRId64 ")", \
4080  sinteger, fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, dst_type, "<INVALID>"), \
4081  (int64_t) _type ## _MIN, (int64_t) _type ## _MAX); \
4082  return -1; \
4083  } \
4084  } while (0)
4085 
4086  switch (dst_type) {
4087  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
4088  IN_RANGE_UNSIGNED(UINT8);
4089  dst->vb_uint8 = (uint8_t)uinteger;
4090  break;
4091 
4092  case FR_TYPE_UINT16:
4093  IN_RANGE_UNSIGNED(UINT16);
4094  dst->vb_uint16 = (uint16_t)uinteger;
4095  break;
4096 
4097  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
4098  IN_RANGE_UNSIGNED(UINT32);
4099  dst->vb_uint32 = (uint32_t)uinteger;
4100  break;
4101 
4102  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
4103  /* IN_RANGE_UNSIGNED doesn't work here */
4104  dst->vb_uint64 = (uint64_t)uinteger;
4105  break;
4106 
4107  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
4108  IN_RANGE_SIGNED(INT8);
4109  dst->vb_int8 = (int8_t)sinteger;
4110  break;
4111 
4112  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
4113  IN_RANGE_SIGNED(INT16);
4114  dst->vb_int16 = (int16_t)sinteger;
4115  break;
4116 
4117  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
4118  IN_RANGE_SIGNED(INT32);
4119  dst->vb_int32 = (int32_t)sinteger;
4120  break;
4121 
4122  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
4123  /* IN_RANGE_SIGNED doesn't work here */

4155 {
4156  size_t len;
4157  ssize_t ret;
4158  char buffer[256];
4159 
4160  if (!fr_cond_assert(*dst_type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return -1;
4161 
4162  len = (inlen < 0) ? strlen(in) : (size_t)inlen;
4163 
4164  /*
4165  * Set size for all fixed length attributes.
4166  */
4167  ret = dict_attr_sizes[*dst_type][1]; /* Max length */
4168 
4169  /*
4170  * Lookup any names before continuing
4171  */
4172  if (dst_enumv) {
4173  char *tmp = NULL;
4174  char *name;
4175  size_t name_len;
4176  fr_dict_enum_t *enumv;
4177 
4178  if (len > (sizeof(buffer) - 1)) {
4179  name_len = fr_value_str_aunescape(NULL, &tmp,
4180  &FR_SBUFF_IN(in, len), SIZE_MAX, quote);
4181  name = tmp;
4182  } else {
4183  name_len = fr_value_str_unescape(&FR_SBUFF_OUT(buffer, sizeof(buffer)),
4184  &FR_SBUFF_IN(in, len), SIZE_MAX, quote);
4185  name = buffer;
4186  }
4187  fr_assert(name);
4188 
4189  enumv = fr_dict_enum_by_name(dst_enumv, name, name_len);
4190  if (tmp) talloc_free(tmp);
4191  if (!enumv) goto parse;
4192 
4193  fr_value_box_copy(ctx, dst, enumv->value);
4194  dst->enumv = dst_enumv;
4195 
4196  return 0;
4197  }
4198 
4199 parse:
4200  /*
4201  * It's a variable ret src->dst_type so we just alloc a new buffer
4202  * of size len and copy.
4203  */
4204  switch (*dst_type) {
4205  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
4206  {
4207  char *buff;
4208 
4209  ret = fr_value_str_aunescape(ctx, &buff, &FR_SBUFF_IN(in, len), SIZE_MAX, quote);
4210  talloc_get_type_abort(buff, char);
4211  dst->vb_strvalue = buff;
4212  }
4213  goto finish;
4214 
4215  /* raw octets: 0x01020304... */
4216  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
4217  {
4218  uint8_t *p;
4219 
4220  /*
4221  * No 0x prefix, just copy verbatim.
4222  */
4223  if ((len < 2) || (strncasecmp(in, "0x", 2) != 0)) {
4224  dst->vb_octets = talloc_memdup(ctx, (uint8_t const *)in, len);
4225  talloc_set_type(dst->vb_octets, uint8_t);
4226  ret = len;
4227  goto finish;
4228  }
4229 
4230  len -= 2;
4231 
4232  /*
4233  * Invalid.
4234  */
4235  if ((len & 0x01) != 0) {
4236  fr_strerror_printf("Length of hex string is not even, got %zu bytes", len);
4237  return -1;
4238  }
4239 
4240  ret = len >> 1;
4241  p = talloc_array(ctx, uint8_t, ret);
4242  if (fr_hex2bin(NULL, &FR_DBUFF_TMP(p, ret), &FR_SBUFF_IN(in + 2, len), false) != (ssize_t)ret) {
4243  talloc_free(p);
4244  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid hex data");
4245  return -1;
4246  }
4247 
4248  dst->vb_octets = p;
4249  }
4250  goto finish;
4251 
4252  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
4253  {
4254  fr_ipaddr_t addr;
4255 
4256  if (fr_inet_pton4(&addr, in, inlen, fr_hostname_lookups, false, true) < 0) return -1;
4257 
4258  /*
4259  * We allow v4 addresses to have a /32 suffix as some databases (PostgreSQL)
4260  * print them this way.
4261  */
4262  if (addr.prefix != 32) {
4263  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid IPv4 mask length \"/%i\". Only \"/32\" permitted "
4264  "for non-prefix types", addr.prefix);
4265  return -1;
4266  }
4267 
4268  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip, &addr, sizeof(dst->vb_ip));
4269  }
4270  goto finish;
4271 
4272  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
4273  if (fr_inet_pton4(&dst->vb_ip, in, inlen, fr_hostname_lookups, false, true) < 0) return -1;
4274  goto finish;
4275 
4276  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
4277  {
4278  fr_ipaddr_t addr;
4279 
4280  if (fr_inet_pton6(&addr, in, inlen, fr_hostname_lookups, false, true) < 0) return -1;
4281 
4282  /*
4283  * We allow v6 addresses to have a /128 suffix as some databases (PostgreSQL)
4284  * print them this way.
4285  */
4286  if (addr.prefix != 128) {
4287  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid IPv6 mask length \"/%i\". Only \"/128\" permitted "
4288  "for non-prefix types", addr.prefix);
4289  return -1;
4290  }
4291 
4292  memcpy(&dst->vb_ip, &addr, sizeof(dst->vb_ip));
4293  }
4294  goto finish;
4295 
4296  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
4297  if (fr_inet_pton6(&dst->vb_ip, in, inlen, fr_hostname_lookups, false, true) < 0) return -1;
4298  goto finish;
4299 
4300  /*
4301  * Dealt with below
4302  */
4303  default:
4304  break;
4305 
4306  case FR_TYPE_STRUCTURAL:
4307  case FR_TYPE_BAD:
4308  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid dst_type %s",
4309  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, *dst_type, "<INVALID>"));
4310  return -1;
4311  }
4312 
4313  /*
4314  * It's a fixed size src->dst_type, copy to a temporary buffer and
4315  * \0 terminate if insize >= 0.
4316  */
4317  if (inlen > 0) {
4318  if (len >= sizeof(buffer)) {
4319  fr_strerror_printf("Temporary buffer too small");
4320  return -1;
4321  }
4322 
4323  memcpy(buffer, in, inlen);
4324  buffer[inlen] = '\0';
4325  in = buffer;
4326  }
4327 
4328  switch (*dst_type) {
4329  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
4330  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
4331  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
4332  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
4333  break;
4334 
4335  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
4336  case FR_TYPE_UINT16:
4337  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
4338  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
4339  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
4340  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
4341  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
4342  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
4343  if (fr_value_box_from_integer_str(dst, *dst_type, in) < 0) return -1;
4344  break;
4345 
4346  case FR_TYPE_SIZE:
4347  if (fr_size_from_str(&dst->datum.size, in) < 0) return -1;
4348  break;
4349 
4350  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
4351  if (dst_enumv) {
4352  if (fr_time_delta_from_str(&dst->datum.time_delta, in, dst_enumv->flags.type_size) < 0) return -1;
4353  } else {
4354  if (fr_time_delta_from_str(&dst->datum.time_delta, in, FR_TIME_RES_SEC) < 0) return -1;
4355  }
4356  break;
4357 
4358  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT32:
4359  {
4360  float f;
4361 
4362  if (sscanf(in, "%f", &f) != 1) {
4363  fr_strerror_printf("Failed parsing \"%s\" as a float32", in);
4364  return -1;
4365  }
4366  dst->vb_float32 = f;
4367  }
4368  break;
4369 
4370  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT64:
4371  {
4372  double d;
4373 
4374  if (sscanf(in, "%lf", &d) != 1) {
4375  fr_strerror_printf("Failed parsing \"%s\" as a float64", in);
4376  return -1;
4377  }
4378  dst->vb_float64 = d;
4379  }
4380  break;
4381 
4382  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
4383  {
4384  if (fr_unix_time_from_str(&dst->vb_date, in) < 0) return -1;
4385 
4386  dst->enumv = dst_enumv;
4387  }
4388  break;
4389 
4390  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
4391  if (fr_inet_ifid_pton((void *) dst->vb_ifid, in) == NULL) {
4392  fr_strerror_printf("Failed to parse interface-id string \"%s\"", in);
4393  return -1;
4394  }
4395  break;
4396 
4397  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
4398  {
4399  char const *c1, *c2, *cp;
4400  size_t p_len = 0;
4401 
4402  /*
4403  * Convert things which are obviously integers to Ethernet addresses
4404  *
4405  * We assume the number is the decimal
4406  * representation of the ethernet address.
4407  * i.e. the ethernet address converted to a
4408  * number, and printed.
4409  *
4410  * The string gets converted to a network-order
4411  * 8-byte number, and then the lower bytes of
4412  * that get copied to the ethernet address.
4413  */
4414  if (is_integer(in)) {
4415  uint64_t lvalue = htonll(atoll(in));
4416 
4417  memcpy(dst->vb_ether, ((uint8_t *) &lvalue) + 2, sizeof(dst->vb_ether));
4418  break;
4419  }
4420 
4421  cp = in;
4422  while (*cp) {
4423  if (cp[1] == ':') {
4424  c1 = hextab;
4425  c2 = memchr(hextab, tolower((int) cp[0]), 16);
4426  cp += 2;
4427  } else if ((cp[1] != '\0') && ((cp[2] == ':') || (cp[2] == '\0'))) {
4428  c1 = memchr(hextab, tolower((int) cp[0]), 16);
4429  c2 = memchr(hextab, tolower((int) cp[1]), 16);
4430  cp += 2;
4431  if (*cp == ':') cp++;
4432  } else {
4433  c1 = c2 = NULL;
4434  }
4435  if (!c1 || !c2 || (p_len >= sizeof(dst->vb_ether))) {
4436  fr_strerror_printf("failed to parse Ethernet address \"%s\"", in);
4437  return -1;
4438  }
4439  dst->vb_ether[p_len] = ((c1-hextab)<<4) + (c2-hextab);
4440  p_len++;
4441  }
4442  }
4443  break;
4444 
4445  /*
4446  * Crazy polymorphic (IPv4/IPv6) attribute src->dst_type for WiMAX.
4447  *
4448  * We try and make is saner by replacing the original
4449  * da, with either an IPv4 or IPv6 da src->dst_type.
4450  *
4451  * These are not dynamic da, and will have the same vendor
4452  * and attribute as the original.
4453  */
4454  case FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_ADDR:
4455  {
4456  if (fr_inet_pton(&dst->vb_ip, in, inlen, AF_UNSPEC, fr_hostname_lookups, true) < 0) return -1;
4457  switch (dst->vb_ip.af) {
4458  case AF_INET:
4459  ret = dict_attr_sizes[FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_ADDR][0]; /* size of IPv4 address */
4460  *dst_type = FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR;
4461  break;
4462 
4463  case AF_INET6:
4464  *dst_type = FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR;
4465  ret = dict_attr_sizes[FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_ADDR][1]; /* size of IPv6 address */
4466  break;
4467 
4468  default:
4469  fr_strerror_printf("Bad address family %i", dst->vb_ip.af);
4470  return -1;
4471  }
4472  }
4473  break;
4474 
4475  case FR_TYPE_BOOL:
4476  if ((strcmp(in, "yes") == 0) || strcmp(in, "true") == 0) {
4477  dst->datum.boolean = true;
4478  } else if ((strcmp(in, "no") == 0) || (strcmp(in, "false") == 0)) {
4479  dst->datum.boolean = false;
4480  } else {
4481  fr_strerror_printf("\"%s\" is not a valid boolean value", in);
4482  return -1;
4483  }
4484  break;
4485 
4486  case FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_PREFIX:
4487  break;
4488 
4489  case FR_TYPE_VALUE_BOX:
4490  case FR_TYPE_VARIABLE_SIZE: /* Should have been dealt with above */
4491  case FR_TYPE_STRUCTURAL: /* Listed again to suppress compiler warnings */
4492  case FR_TYPE_BAD:
4493  fr_strerror_printf("Unknown attribute dst_type %d", *dst_type);
4494  return -1;
4495  }
4496 
4497 finish:
4498  dst->vb_length = ret;
4499  dst->type = *dst_type;
4500  dst->tainted = tainted;
4501 
4502  /*
4503  * Fixup enumvs
4504  */
4505  dst->enumv = dst_enumv;
4506  dst->next = NULL;
4507 
4508  return 0;
4509 }
