4511 /** Print one boxed value to a string
4512  *
4513  * This function should primarily be used when a #fr_value_box_t is being
4514  * serialized in some non-standard way, i.e. as a value for a field
4515  * in a database, in all other instances it's better to use
4516  * #fr_value_box_print_quoted.
4517  *
4518  * @param[in] out Where to write the printed string.
4519  * @param[in] data Value box to print.
4520  * @param[in] e_rules To apply to FR_TYPE_STRING types.
4521  * Is not currently applied to any other box type.
4522  */
4523 ssize_t fr_value_box_print(fr_sbuff_t *out, fr_value_box_t const *data, fr_sbuff_escape_rules_t const *e_rules)
4524 {
4525  fr_sbuff_t our_out = FR_SBUFF_NO_ADVANCE(out);
4526 
4527  char buf[1024]; /* Interim buffer to use with poorly behaved printing functions */
4528 
4529  if (!fr_cond_assert(data->type != FR_TYPE_INVALID)) return 0;
4530 
4531  if (data->enumv && data->enumv->name) {
4532  char const *name;
4533 
4534  name = fr_dict_enum_name_by_value(data->enumv, data);
4535  if (name) {
4536  FR_SBUFF_IN_ESCAPE_BUFFER_RETURN(&our_out, name, NULL);
4537  goto done;
4538  }
4539  }
4540 
4541  switch (data->type) {
4542  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
4543  if (data->vb_length) FR_SBUFF_IN_ESCAPE_RETURN(&our_out,
4544  data->vb_strvalue, data->vb_length, e_rules);
4545  break;
4546 
4547  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
4548  FR_SBUFF_IN_CHAR_RETURN(&our_out, '0', 'x');
4549  if (data->vb_length) FR_SBUFF_RETURN(fr_bin2hex, &our_out,
4550  &FR_DBUFF_TMP(data->vb_octets, data->vb_length), SIZE_MAX);
4551  break;
4552 
4553  /*
4554  * We need to use the proper inet_ntop functions for IP
4555  * addresses, else the output might not match output of
4556  * other functions, which makes testing difficult.
4557  *
4558  * An example is tunneled ipv4 in ipv6 addresses.
4559  */
4560  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_ADDR:
4561  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_ADDR:
4562  if (!fr_inet_ntop(buf, sizeof(buf), &data->vb_ip)) return 0;
4563  FR_SBUFF_IN_STRCPY_RETURN(&our_out, buf);
4564  break;
4565 
4566  case FR_TYPE_IPV4_PREFIX:
4567  case FR_TYPE_IPV6_PREFIX:
4568  if (!fr_inet_ntop_prefix(buf, sizeof(buf), &data->vb_ip)) return 0;
4569  FR_SBUFF_IN_STRCPY_RETURN(&our_out, buf);
4570  break;
4571 
4572  case FR_TYPE_IFID:
4573  if (!fr_inet_ifid_ntop(buf, sizeof(buf), data->vb_ifid)) return 0;
4574  FR_SBUFF_IN_STRCPY_RETURN(&our_out, buf);
4575  break;
4576 
4577  case FR_TYPE_ETHERNET:
4578  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x",
4579  data->vb_ether[0], data->vb_ether[1],
4580  data->vb_ether[2], data->vb_ether[3],
4581  data->vb_ether[4], data->vb_ether[5]);
4582  break;
4583 
4584  case FR_TYPE_BOOL:
4585  FR_SBUFF_IN_STRCPY_RETURN(&our_out, data->vb_uint8 ? "yes" : "no");
4586  break;
4587 
4588  case FR_TYPE_UINT8:
4589  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%u", data->vb_uint8);
4590  break;
4591 
4592  case FR_TYPE_UINT16:
4593  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%u", data->vb_uint16);
4594  break;
4595 
4596  case FR_TYPE_UINT32:
4597  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%u", data->vb_uint32);
4598  break;
4599 
4600  case FR_TYPE_UINT64:
4601  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%" PRIu64, data->vb_uint64);
4602  break;
4603 
4604  case FR_TYPE_INT8:
4605  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%d", data->vb_int8);
4606  break;
4607 
4608  case FR_TYPE_INT16:
4609  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%d", data->vb_int16);
4610  break;
4611 
4612  case FR_TYPE_INT32:
4613  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%d", data->vb_int32);
4614  break;
4615 
4616  case FR_TYPE_INT64:
4617  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%" PRId64, data->vb_int64);
4618  break;
4619 
4620  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT32:
4621  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%f", (double) data->vb_float32);
4622  break;
4623 
4624  case FR_TYPE_FLOAT64:
4625  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%g", data->vb_float64);
4626  break;
4627 
4628  case FR_TYPE_DATE:
4629  {
4630  int64_t subseconds;
4631  time_t t;
4632  struct tm s_tm;
4633  size_t len;
4634 
4635  t = fr_unix_time_to_sec(data->vb_date);
4636  (void) gmtime_r(&t, &s_tm);
4637 
4638  if (!data->enumv || (data->enumv->flags.type_size == FR_TIME_RES_SEC)) {
4639  len = strftime(buf, sizeof(buf), "%b %e %Y %H:%M:%S UTC", &s_tm);
4640  FR_SBUFF_IN_BSTRNCPY_RETURN(&our_out, buf, len);
4641  goto done;
4642  }
4643 
4644  len = strftime(buf, sizeof(buf), "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S", &s_tm);
4645  FR_SBUFF_IN_BSTRNCPY_RETURN(&our_out, buf, len);
4646  subseconds = data->vb_date % NSEC;
4647 
4648  /*
4649  * Use RFC 3339 format, which is a
4650  * profile of ISO8601. The ISO standard
4651  * allows a much more complex set of date
4652  * formats. The RFC is much stricter.
4653  */
4654  switch (data->enumv->flags.type_size) {
4655  default:
4656  break;
4657 
4658  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
4659  subseconds /= 1000000;
4660  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, ".%03" PRIi64, subseconds);
4661  break;
4662 
4663  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
4664  subseconds /= 1000;
4665  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, ".%06" PRIi64, subseconds);
4666  break;
4667 
4668  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
4669  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, ".%09" PRIi64, subseconds);
4670  break;
4671  }
4672 
4673  /*
4674  * And time zone.
4675  */
4676  if (s_tm.tm_gmtoff != 0) {
4677  int hours, minutes;
4678 
4679  hours = s_tm.tm_gmtoff / 3600;
4680  minutes = (s_tm.tm_gmtoff / 60) % 60;
4681 
4682  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%+03d:%02u", hours, minutes);
4683  } else {
4684  FR_SBUFF_IN_CHAR_RETURN(&our_out, 'Z');
4685  }
4686  break;
4687  }
4688 
4689  case FR_TYPE_SIZE:
4690  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%zu", data->datum.size);
4691  break;
4692 
4693  case FR_TYPE_TIME_DELTA:
4694  {
4695  char *q;
4696  uint64_t lhs, rhs;
4697  fr_time_res_t res = FR_TIME_RES_SEC;
4698 
4699  if (data->enumv) res = data->enumv->flags.type_size;
4700 
4701  switch (res) {
4702  default:
4703  case FR_TIME_RES_SEC:
4704  lhs = data->datum.time_delta / NSEC;
4705  rhs = data->datum.time_delta % NSEC;
4706  break;
4707 
4708  case FR_TIME_RES_MSEC:
4709  lhs = data->datum.time_delta / 1000000;
4710  rhs = data->datum.time_delta % 1000000;
4711  break;
4712 
4713  case FR_TIME_RES_USEC:
4714  lhs = data->datum.time_delta / 1000;
4715  rhs = data->datum.time_delta % 1000;
4716  break;
4717 
4718  case FR_TIME_RES_NSEC:
4719  lhs = data->datum.time_delta;
4720  rhs = 0;
4721  break;
4722  }
4723 
4724  FR_SBUFF_IN_SPRINTF_RETURN(&our_out, "%" PRIu64 ".%09" PRIu64, lhs, rhs);
4725  q = fr_sbuff_current(&our_out) - 1;
4726 
4727  /*
4728  * Truncate trailing zeros.
4729  */
4730  while (*q == '0') *(q--) = '\0';
4731 
4732  /*
4733  * If there's nothing after the decimal point,
4734  * trunctate the decimal point. i.e. Don't print
4735  * "5."
4736  */
4737  if (*q == '.') {
4738  *q = '\0';
4739  } else {
4740  q++; /* to account for q-- above */
4741  }
4742  fr_sbuff_set(&our_out, q);
4743  }
4744  break;
4745 
4746  case FR_TYPE_GROUP:
4747  {
4748  fr_value_box_t vb;
4749  ssize_t slen;
4750 
4751  memset(&vb, 0, sizeof(vb));
4752 
4753  /*
4754  * Be lazy by just converting it to a string, and then printing the string.
4755  */
4756  if (fr_value_box_cast_to_strvalue(NULL, &vb, FR_TYPE_STRING, NULL, data->vb_group) < 0) return 0;
4757 
4758  slen = fr_value_box_print(&our_out, &vb, e_rules);
4759  fr_value_box_clear(&vb);
4760  if (slen < 0) return slen;
4761  }
4762  break;
4763 
4764  /*
4765  * Don't add default here
4766  */
4767  case FR_TYPE_TLV: /* Not a box type */
4768  case FR_TYPE_STRUCT: /* Not a box type */
4769  case FR_TYPE_VSA: /* Not a box type */
4770  case FR_TYPE_VENDOR: /* Not a box type */
4771  case FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_ADDR:
4772  case FR_TYPE_COMBO_IP_PREFIX:
4773  case FR_TYPE_VALUE_BOX:
4774  case FR_TYPE_BAD:

4811 /** Concatenate a list of value boxes
4812  *
4813  * @note Will automatically cast all #fr_value_box_t to type specified.
4814  *
4815  * @param[in] ctx to allocate new value buffer in.
4816  * @param[out] out Where to write the resulting box.
4817  * @param[in] list to concatenate together.
4818  * @param[in] type May be #FR_TYPE_STRING or #FR_TYPE_OCTETS, no other types are
4819  * supported.
4820  * @param[in] free_input If true, free the input boxes.
4821  * @return
4822  * - 0 on success.
4823  * - -1 on failure.
4824  */
4825 int fr_value_box_list_concat(TALLOC_CTX *ctx,
4826  fr_value_box_t *out, fr_value_box_t **list, fr_type_t type, bool free_input)
4827 {
4828  TALLOC_CTX *pool;
4829  fr_cursor_t cursor;
4830  fr_value_box_t const *vb;
4831 
4832  if (!list || !*list) {
4833  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid arguments. List was NULL");
4834  return -1;
4835  }
4836 
4837  switch (type) {
4838  case FR_TYPE_STRING:
4839  case FR_TYPE_OCTETS:
4840  break;
4841 
4842  default:
4843  fr_strerror_printf("Invalid argument. Can't concatenate boxes to type %s",
4844  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_value_box_type_table, type, "<INVALID>"));
4845  return -1;
4846  }
4847 
4848  fr_cursor_init(&cursor, list);
4849 
4850  /*
4851  * Allow concatenating in place
4852  */
4853  if (out == *list) {
4854  if ((*list)->type != type) {
4855  fr_value_box_t from_cast;
4856  fr_value_box_t *next = out->next;
4857 
4858  /*
4859  * Two phase, as the casting code doesn't
4860  * allow 'cast-in-place'.
4861  */
4862  if (fr_value_box_cast(ctx, &from_cast, type, NULL, out) < 0) return -1;
4863  if (fr_value_box_copy(ctx, out, &from_cast) < 0) return -1;
4864  out->next = next; /* Restore the next pointer */
4865  }
4866  fr_cursor_next(&cursor);
4867  } else {
4868  if (fr_value_box_cast(ctx, out, type, NULL, *list) < 0) return -1; /* Decomposes to copy */
4869 
4870  if (free_input) {
4871  fr_cursor_free_item(&cursor); /* Advances cursor */
4872  } else {
4873  fr_cursor_next(&cursor);
4874  }
4875  }
4876 
4877  /*
4878  * Imploding a one element list.
4879  */
4880  if (!fr_cursor_current(&cursor)) return 0;
4881 
4882  pool = talloc_pool(NULL, 255); /* To absorb the temporary strings */
4883 
4884  /*
4885  * Join the remaining values
4886  */
4887  while ((vb = fr_cursor_current(&cursor))) {
4888  fr_value_box_t from_cast;
4889  fr_value_box_t const *n;
4890 
4891  if (vb->type != type) {
4892  talloc_free_children(pool); /* Clear out previous buffers */
4893  memset(&from_cast, 0, sizeof(from_cast));
4894 
4895  if (fr_value_box_cast(pool, &from_cast, type, NULL, vb) < 0) {
4896  error:
4897  talloc_free(pool);
4898  return -1;
4899  }
4900 
4901  n = &from_cast;
4902  } else {
4903  n = vb;
4904  }
4905 
4906  /*
4907  * Append the next value
4908  */
4909  if (type == FR_TYPE_STRING) {
4910  if (fr_value_box_bstrn_append(ctx, out, n->vb_strvalue, n->vb_length, n->tainted) < 0) goto error;
4911  } else {
4912  if (fr_value_box_mem_append(ctx, out, n->vb_octets, n->vb_length, n->tainted) < 0) goto error;
4913  }
4914 
4915  if (free_input) {
4916  fr_cursor_free_item(&cursor); /* Advances cursor */
4917  } else {
4918  fr_cursor_next(&cursor);
4919  }
4920  }
4921 
4922  talloc_free(pool);
4923 
4924  return 0;
4925 }

4927 /** Concatenate the string representations of a list of value boxes together
4928  *
4929  * @param[in] ctx to allocate the buffer in.
4930  * @param[in] head of the list of value boxes.
4931  * @param[in] delim to insert between value box values.
4932  * @param[in] e_rules to control escaping of the concatenated elements.
4933  * @return
4934  * - NULL on error.
4935  * - The concatenation of the string values of the value box list on success.
4936  */
4937 char *fr_value_box_list_aprint(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, fr_value_box_t const *head, char const *delim,
4938  fr_sbuff_escape_rules_t const *e_rules)
4939 {
4940  fr_value_box_t const *vb = head;
4941  char *aggr, *td = NULL;
4942  TALLOC_CTX *pool = NULL;
4943 
4944  if (!head) return NULL;
4945 
4946  fr_value_box_aprint(ctx, &aggr, vb, e_rules);
4947  if (!aggr) return NULL;
4948  if (!vb->next) return aggr;
4949 
4950  /*
4951  * If we're aggregating more values,
4952  * allocate a temporary pool.
4953  */
4954  pool = talloc_pool(NULL, 255);
4955  if (delim) td = talloc_typed_strdup(pool, delim);
4956 
4957  while ((vb = vb->next)) {
4958  char *str, *new_aggr;
4959 
4960  fr_value_box_aprint(pool, &str, vb, e_rules);
4961  if (!str) continue;
4962 
4963  new_aggr = talloc_buffer_append_variadic_buffer(ctx, aggr, 2, td, str);
4964  if (unlikely(!new_aggr)) {
4965  talloc_free(aggr);
4966  talloc_free(pool);
4967  return NULL;
4968  }
4969  aggr = new_aggr;
4970  talloc_free(str);
4971  }
4972  talloc_free(pool);
4973 
4974  return aggr;
4975 }

4999 /** Flatten a list into individual "char *" argv-style array
5000  *
5001  * @param[in] ctx to allocate boxes in.
5002  * @param[out] argv_p where output strings go
5003  * @param[in] in boxes to flatten
5004  * @return
5005  * - >= 0 number of array elements in argv
5006  * - <0 on error
5007  */
5008 int fr_value_box_list_flatten_argv(TALLOC_CTX *ctx, char ***argv_p, fr_value_box_t const *in)
5009 {
5010  int i, argc;
5011  char **argv;
5012 
5013  if (in->type != FR_TYPE_GROUP) {
5014  argc = 1;
5015 
5016  } else {
5017  argc = fr_value_box_list_len(in);
5018  }
5019 
5020  argv = talloc_zero_array(ctx, char *, argc + 1);
5021  if (!argv) return -1;
5022 
5023  if (in->type != FR_TYPE_GROUP) {
5024  fr_value_box_aprint(argv, &argv[0], in, NULL);
5025  } else {
5026  fr_value_box_t const *in_p;
5027 
5028  /*
5029  * Print the children of each group into the argv array.
5030  */
5031  for (in_p = in, i = 0;
5032  in_p;
5033  in_p = in_p->next) {
5034  fr_value_box_aprint(argv, &argv[i], in_p->vb_group, NULL);
5035  if (!argv[i]) {
5036  talloc_free(argv);
5037  return -1;
5038  }
5039 
5040  /*
5041  * Unescape quoted strings, so that the
5042  * programs get passed the unquoted
5043  * results.
5044  */
5045  if ((argv[i][0] == '"') || (argv[i][0] == '\'')) {
5046  size_t inlen = talloc_array_length(argv[i]);
5047  fr_value_substr_unescape(&FR_SBUFF_OUT(argv[i], inlen),
5048  &FR_SBUFF_IN(argv[i] + 1, inlen - 1),
5049  SIZE_MAX, *argv[i]);
5050  }
5051 
5052  i++;
5053  }
5054  }
5055 
5056  *argv_p = argv;
5057  return argc;
5058 }
